Black Friday is still in its infancy in South Africa but has taken the nation by storm. This year consumers are eagerly awaiting the one day of the year with “real” sales where consumers can save up to 70%. Loot.co.za is one of SA’s top general online merchants with over 14 million products across 17 merchandise categories. This year they have some of the best deals and are excited to provide consumers with a wide range of products at once-off incredible discounts. Each day from Monday 25 November through to Black Friday loot.co.za is releasing hot teaser deals, with the big reveal launching at midnight on 29 November. New offers will be dropped continuously throughout the period ending on 2 December 2019. Loot.co.za CEO Greg LeRoux, stated that they are thrilled to be partnering with big brands such as Samsung, Garmin, JVC, JBL, Huawei, Hisense and many more. He further said that the big items creating a buzz this year are TVs, wearables, media boxes, appliances, homeware and more. The hottest items include a Samsung 55-inch QLED TV from only R11,000, JVC headphones, the Garmin Forerunner and Mediabox. This is the first year in which loot.co.za is offering their Marketplace sellers a chance to cash in on the action and as a result are providing their customers with even more value and a much wider range of products from décor, jewellery, electronics, DIY, and sports to toys, tents and so much more. The vast merchandise offering coupled with 13 different payment options makes loot.co.za one of the most convenient places to shop for Black Friday 2019 deals. In order to qualify for free delivery, you only need a total basket value of R350, truly making loot.co.za one of the most affordable online retailers in South Africa. Don’t miss out on these deals brought to you by loot.co.za R14,999 – Save R14,000 Click here to get the deal <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-329653" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/deal-1.png" alt="" width="